Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, has commiserated with the Governor of Borno State, Babagana Zulum, over the death of his Chief of Staff, Dr. Babagana Wakil. DAILY POST had reported that Babagana Wakil died on Wednesday morning. Spokesperson to the Governor of Borno States, Isa Gusau, did not disclose the cause of his death Reacting, Lawan sent his condolence in a statement by his Special Adviser (Media) Ola Awoniyi on Wednesday. He also consoled Wakiliâ€™s family and the government, people of Borno over the sad loss. According to him, Dr. Wakil was a loyal and trusted aide to the Governor, who had made a great contribution to the efforts of the state government in rebuilding a state that has been devastated by several years of a mindless insurgency. Lawan prayed that Allah will forgive the shortcomings of the departed and grant his family the fortitude to bear his painful loss.